On the day that we found Kao’s body,

00:15:41.880 --> 00:15:44.440
I encountered the suspect who was ambushing on us.

00:15:45.720 --> 00:15:48.600
While I was about to arrest him,

00:15:48.800 --> 00:15:51.320
he resisted and tried to fight back.

00:15:51.880 --> 00:15:55.000
It was then that I got a glimpse of the tattoo on his arm.

00:15:55.720 --> 00:15:58.360
It’s the same tattoo I saw on the person who killed my parents.

00:16:09.120 --> 00:16:09.920
Hold on.

00:16:10.440 --> 00:16:15.720
Are you saying that Lieut Tam’s and Kao’s cases are related to your parents’ case?

00:16:16.760 --> 00:16:17.640
Yes.

00:16:19.320 --> 00:16:21.840
And the person behind these cases...

00:16:22.760 --> 00:16:24.040
is Montree.

00:16:24.920 --> 00:16:28.040
Do you have any evidence to confirm that Montree is the culprit?

00:16:28.600 --> 00:16:31.120
Those victims are also somewhat conneted to Montree.

00:16:31.960 --> 00:16:34.000
I think we should issue a warrant and summon him for interrogation.

00:16:34.000 --> 00:16:35.160
I only believe in evidence.

00:16:37.120 --> 00:16:39.240
If you want me to believe in what you said,

00:16:40.960 --> 00:16:42.000
go and find me the evidence.

00:16:46.480 --> 00:16:48.600
I’m going to warn you for the last time.

00:16:49.320 --> 00:16:51.720
If you can’t separate work from personal matters,

00:16:53.240 --> 00:16:55.400
I’ll have you removed from this case.

00:16:59.000 --> 00:17:01.400
You have to calm down, Tharn.

00:17:01.480 --> 00:17:03.400
Don’t argue with Inspector Akk or try to challenge him.

00:17:04.800 --> 00:17:06.760
I don’t know if you’d listen to me.

00:17:06.760 --> 00:17:09.040
But please calm down and think twice about that gunman.

00:17:09.800 --> 00:17:13.000
Otherwise, Inspector will give you an earful about it again.

00:17:13.640 --> 00:17:16.040
You still don’t have a solid evidence too.

00:17:16.880 --> 00:17:18.280
So, stop overthinking about it.

00:17:18.280 --> 00:17:20.240
But I’m sure it’s the same person.

00:17:22.200 --> 00:17:24.560
And I will find the evidence to confirm it.

00:17:25.240 --> 00:17:26.280
Where are you going?

00:17:27.599 --> 00:17:30.800
To see someone who can help me find the evidence about my father’s case.

00:17:40.680 --> 00:17:44.320
I’ve gathered all the information about your father’s case.

00:17:44.680 --> 00:17:46.600
They’re all in here...

00:17:48.440 --> 00:17:50.200
including the list of your father’s colleagues too.

00:17:51.640 --> 00:17:55.040
Don’t tell anyone especially the Inspector that I did this for you.

00:17:56.240 --> 00:17:57.440
I know that.

00:17:58.640 --> 00:18:00.480
I promise not to get you into trouble.

00:18:01.000 --> 00:18:02.840
Inspector will never know about this.

00:18:04.800 --> 00:18:05.720
Hold on.

00:18:09.640 --> 00:18:10.480
What is it?

00:18:12.280 --> 00:18:14.200
I don’t know if I should tell you this.

00:18:15.240 --> 00:18:16.600
I think this case is...

00:18:17.760 --> 00:18:19.880
probably connected to a much bigger one.

00:18:23.520 --> 00:18:24.680
The Inspector’s older brother…

00:18:26.840 --> 00:18:30.280
was your father’s right-hand man, the one who took care of Montree’s case.

00:18:35.840 --> 00:18:37.360
Are you serious?

00:18:48.680 --> 00:18:50.360
Is this Inspector’s brother?

00:18:52.280 --> 00:18:56.000
Why doesn’t Inspector tell you that he knew your father?

00:18:56.440 --> 00:18:58.040
Lieut Itt killed himself...

00:18:59.480 --> 00:19:00.960
because he was caught for taking bribe.

00:19:02.920 --> 00:19:04.320
And the one who looked after this case...

00:19:06.320 --> 00:19:07.720
was your father.

00:20:02.200 --> 00:20:04.440
Are you sure you’re not going to come and live with me?

00:20:06.680 --> 00:20:08.000
Thank you so much, Uncle.

00:20:08.000 --> 00:20:09.840
But I really don’t want to bother you.

00:20:10.240 --> 00:20:11.440
It’s not a bother at all.

00:20:11.920 --> 00:20:13.720
Both you and Itt are like my own sons.

00:20:14.480 --> 00:20:15.800
You’re like a family to me.

00:20:16.280 --> 00:20:19.280
Itt also asked me to take care of you.

00:20:19.960 --> 00:20:23.920
You have done much enough for me, Uncle

00:20:24.640 --> 00:20:27.760
And don’t worry about your education.

00:20:28.520 --> 00:20:29.760
I’ll take care of that.

00:20:30.640 --> 00:20:33.480
I already told you that you’re like a son to me.

00:20:34.360 --> 00:20:35.400
Okay?

00:21:37.320 --> 00:21:38.680
Is it Korn who did this?

00:21:39.520 --> 00:21:40.200
Yes.

00:21:40.400 --> 00:21:42.120
Do you want me to arrest him?

00:21:43.160 --> 00:21:44.080
Not yet.

00:21:44.280 --> 00:21:46.040
I don’t want to ruin our big case.

00:21:47.000 --> 00:21:48.880
Keep investigating on the drugs case.

00:21:50.200 --> 00:21:51.920
And try to be especially careful during this time.

00:21:53.320 --> 00:21:55.600
One of our teams is investigating about Korn.

00:21:56.400 --> 00:21:57.160
Yes, Inspector.

00:22:22.040 --> 00:22:25.320
Doctor, how’s my brother doing?

00:22:25.480 --> 00:22:27.800
He’s stable right now.

00:22:29.920 --> 00:22:31.040
Please excuse me.

00:22:39.160 --> 00:22:40.680
Phaya.

00:22:47.400 --> 00:22:48.320
Nee.

00:22:49.840 --> 00:22:51.720
I’m starting to agree with you.

00:22:52.760 --> 00:22:55.280
That he shouldn’t have become a cop.

00:22:56.280 --> 00:22:58.200
Only bad things happened to him.

00:22:59.480 --> 00:23:01.400
You have to stay strong, Nee.

00:23:01.760 --> 00:23:04.600
So that at least Grandma can lean on you.

00:23:05.840 --> 00:23:07.640
I’m scared for Grandma too.

00:23:09.200 --> 00:23:11.680
